00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:14.500
Today's Video Blog is related to Deaf Truck Drivers and Commercial Drivers Licenses (CDL). 

00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:23.500
My name is Jack Leiker.  I hold a CDL Class A License.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:31.500
Hello deaf truck drivers.  My name is Brenda Palmigiano.  I have a CDL Class A License.

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:40.100
They (deaf) don't need to use a hearing aid to operate the truck,  

00:00:40.200 --> 00:00:41.900
because the trucks have technologies build in.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:46.500
They (deaf) can drive without their hearing aids because the eyes have better reception.

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.500
The writing test is awful.  I had to go back many times to pass the test. 

00:00:54.000 --> 00:01:00.500
The writing test took me 9 times to pass.

00:01:00.600 --> 00:01:05.500
I was not allowed to have an interpreter for the Pre-Trip Inspection tests for the CDL. 

00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:08.500
For that I had to “listen” to listen to a person speak for 10 minutes.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:19.500
VESID believed that I only needed to get a Class B License. 

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.500
So, I had to get my trainer to convince VESID that I needed a Class A License.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:34.500
Brenda and Jack are not alone as there are many others out there like them.  

00:01:35.000 --> 00:01:37.500
This occurs because of a federal regulation. 

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:45.500
US Department of Transportation Federal Motor Carrier Safety Administration (FMCSA)  

